. Line Varoma tray with a sheet of wet, wrung out baking paper keeping some holes uncovered for steam to circulate then pour egg mixture onto it. Cover with Varoma lid then steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 3.<b> Carefully remove Varoma then transfer frittata to a serving plate. Cut in wedges and serve hot or cold.","The word frittata derives from the Italian verb <i>‘friggere’<\/i>, meaning ‘to fry’. It is the Italian equivalent of our omelette made with a variety of different ingredients and flavour combinations, depending on what is on hand. Frittatas can be eaten warm, accompanied by a fresh mixed salad, or sliced and eaten cold as picnic or party food. This simple recipe is brimming with the flavours of fresh spring vegetables and is a great way to use up eggs leftover from other recipes.","To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan cheese for a vegetarian hard cheese.","<b>Serves 8<b> as part of an antipasti board or <b>2-3 for<b> lunch with a side salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","25m","8 slices"]}